                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;You allude to what I think should be the most basic test: &quot;Should this object be usable by code which expects objects of (what would be) the base type&quot;.  If the answer is yes, the object &lt;i&gt;must&lt;/i&gt; inherit.  If no, then it probably should not.  If I had my druthers, languages would provide a keyword to refer to &quot;this class&quot;, and provide a means of defining a class which should behave just like another class, but not be substitutable for it (such a class would have all &quot;this class&quot; references replaced with itself).&lt;/span&gt;

