            &lt;div class=&quot;comment-body js-comment-edit-hide&quot;&gt;

                &lt;span class=&quot;comment-copy&quot;&gt;Even though you mention a good technique, I don&apos;t think you&apos;re answering the question.   It&apos;s not comparing runtime against compile time, but inheritance against composition, which REUSES code from either ONE or MANY classes and can OVERRIDE or ADD new logic. What you describe as object composition, is simply injecting logic via objects assigned as properties in a class, which is a great alternative for runtime manipulation. Thanks!&lt;/span&gt;

              &lt;div class=&quot;d-inline-flex ai-center&quot;&gt;
&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/users/5596912/isaak-eriksson&quot; title=&quot;611 reputation&quot; class=&quot;comment-user&quot;&gt;Isaak Eriksson&lt;/a&gt;
